er the rape actually occurred, Fleisher is forced to confront her own role as a maker of this conflicted history, and to examine the legacy of white women "busybodies."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBear River Massacre, Idaho, 1863. 0aShoshoni IndiansxWars, 1863-1865. 4aAmerican Studies : Indigenous Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aHistory : American History. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780791485200?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791485200423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791485200/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles